<body>
    <h1>1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Introduction to API Designer</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p></p>
<div class=3D"">
<div class=3D"childtabs-macro" data-fixed-position=3D"false">
<div class=3D"aui-tabs horizontal-tabs" data-aui-responsive=3D"true">
<strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data-conte=
nt-id=3D"1203279288">Mesh Platform Overview</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"a754afe0-7384-4b32-acf3-e4bd6c8d=
0746-1203279288">
<p><br></p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper">The Mesh Platform is re=
alised by a suite of interacting subsystems which have specific roles in pr=
oviding services to end-users, manufacturing and running Components.</span>=
</p>
<p>This page will enumerate the coarse-grained subsystems that are required=
 to realise the platform and outline their roles.</p>
<h2 id=3D"MeshPlatformOverview-PlatformSubsystemArchitectureDiagram">Platfo=
rm Subsystem Architecture Diagram</h2>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border" draggable=3D"false" alt=
=3D"Platform Subsystem Architecture" src=3D"2571c4fe7f571ad56053a57b65e51c8=
87a62d774027d72211183e7e89e78531b" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/=
788938853/mesh-overview.png?version=3D3&amp;modificationDate=3D164860134275=
3&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=
=3D"1100362772" data-linked-resource-version=3D"3" data-linked-resource-typ=
e=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"mesh-overview.png" d=
ata-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource=
-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"788938853"=
 data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"9" title=3D"Platform Subsystem A=
rchitecture" width=3D"468" height=3D"313"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"MeshPlatformOverview-Subsystemoverview">Subsystem overview</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Subsystem</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Purpose</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Candid<span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data=
-ref=3D"abde01ee-6c84-4b16-ae9e-c96d01636ae9">ate/Actual Technolo</span>gie=
s</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class=3D"highlight-grey confluenceTd" title=3D"Background colour : Grey=
" colspan=3D"3" data-highlight-colour=3D"grey"><em><strong>Mesh Enablers</s=
trong></em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Container Service</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Provides segregated, scalable compute on-demand =
to run Components</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Azure AKS</strong>, AWS EKS</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Service Discovery</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Allows Components to find and consume other Comp=
onents</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Istio, <strong>Consul Connect</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Egress Gateway</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Mediates calls from platform-hoste=
d Components to off-platform services - sometimes called a Terminating Gate=
way</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Linked to Service Discovery/Servic=
e Mesh</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"highlight-grey confluenceTd" title=3D"Background colour : Grey=
" colspan=3D"3" data-highlight-colour=3D"grey"><em><strong>Platform Interac=
tion Enablers</strong></em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Source Code Repository</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Store Component source code history</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>BitBucket</strong>, GitHub</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Developer Tools</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Command-line tools to work with Components and i=
nteract with the Platform</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Custom build</strong>, Waypoint</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Mesh Connect</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Application to discover, propose and manage Comp=
onent portfolios</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Custom build using Mesh technologies</st=
rong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Management Services</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Support Mesh Connect and Developer Tools and com=
posed automations</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Custom build</strong> w/Datastores</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"highlight-grey confluenceTd" title=3D"Background colour : Grey=
" colspan=3D"3" data-highlight-colour=3D"grey"><em><strong>Software Storage=
, Build &amp; Delivery Enablers</strong></em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Continuous Integration</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Support manufacturing, validating and publishing=
 Component Versions from source</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Bamboo</strong>, Jenkins</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Control Services</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Support deploying/undeploying Component Versions=
 from binary repositories and getting 'state of the world'</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Microservices + Bamboo</strong>, Jenkins=
, Azure/AWS services</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Container Profile Builder</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">A versioned, containerised stack of build tools =
to predictably manufacture binary artifacts for a Component</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Podman, Buildah, Docker, Maven, OpenJDK,=
 NPM</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Component Type Deployers</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">A versioned, containerised stack o=
f deploy tools to predictably deploy Component versions to an environment</=
td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Kubernetes&nbsp;+ Bamboo</=
strong>, Jenkins, Azure/AWS services</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Binary Artifact Repository</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Polyglot repository for storing deployable artif=
acts of Components indefinitely</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Artifactory</strong>, Nexus</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Image Repository</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Docker Image repository for storing runnable ima=
ges of Components and Platform toolchains</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Artifactory</strong>, Docker Registry, A=
zure Container Registry, Amazon ECR</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Configuration Repository</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Stores general and environment-specific configur=
ation settings for Components</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Artifactory</strong>, Database</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Secrets Repository</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Stores sensitive environment-specific configurat=
ion settings for Components</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Artifactory</strong>, Vault, Azure Key-V=
ault</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"highlight-grey confluenceTd" title=3D"Background colour : Grey=
" colspan=3D"3" data-highlight-colour=3D"grey"><em title=3D""><strong>Produ=
ct Enablers</strong></em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">API Gateway</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Traditional Ingress Gateway for APIs enabling of=
f-Mesh systems/applications to invoke APIs</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Axway, <strong>Kong</strong>, Tyk, Azure API Man=
agement, AWS API Gateway</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Event Broker</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Run secure Pub/Sub topics</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Kafka</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">In-memory Cache</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Improve latency issues with slow/low-volume upst=
ream systems by enabling an in-memory cache</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Redis</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Single Page Application Hosting</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Serve up SPA static content and provide security=
 integration to IdP(s)</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>AWS S3 &amp; CloudFront</strong>, Kubern=
etes, OBMR</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">NoSQL Datastore</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Provide persistent datastores for microservices =
in a Data Mesh</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><strong>Cassandra</strong>, MongoDB, CockroachDB=
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"3" class=3D"confluenceTd"><em><strong>Telemetry Enablers</st=
rong></em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Log Analysis</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">System to store all logs from Comp=
onents &amp; subsystems suitable for large scale analysis</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><strong>Splunk&gt;</strong></p>=
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Transaction Observer</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Provide visibility of transactions=
 across components in real-time</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">App Dynamics, Zipkin, Splunk Obser=
vability</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"MeshPlatformOverview-SubsystemServiceQualityAttributes">Subsystem=
 Service Quality Attributes</h2>
<p><br></p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Further reading:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv=
.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=3DMESH&amp;title=3DWestpac+M=
esh+for+Architects" rel=3D"nofollow">Westpac Mesh for Architects</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279290">Multi-Speed API Layering</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"a754afe0-7384-4b32-acf3-e4bd6c8d=
0746-1203279290">
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><span class=3D"confluen=
ce-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggabl=
e=3D"false" src=3D"34b31c022ed95a99209a660bbd86abcfdee0fc3c15da1a6552d125fb=
642100da" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279290/multilayer.PNG=
?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571072507&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unreso=
lved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279291" data-linked=
-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linke=
d-resource-default-alias=3D"multilayer.PNG" data-base-url=3D"https://conflu=
ence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" da=
ta-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279290" data-linked-resource-contain=
er-version=3D"5" alt=3D"" width=3D"468" height=3D"294"></span></span></p>
<p>When designing your solution, divide your components into the following =
distinct layers:</p>
<ol>
<li>Micro Frontends / Experience API - Micro Frontend components combines b=
oth user-interface and Experience API code bases in a single repository. Ex=
perience APIs are tightly coupled to the user-interface design, should not =
be reusable, and should be thrown away when the user-interface they are cou=
pled with is removed. Experience APIs can use capability and information AP=
Is to provide the necessary functionality.</li>
<li>Partner APIs - Partner APIs expose our products and services to compani=
es that we have an established relationship with. Partner APIs use capabili=
ty and information APIs to provide the necessary functionality. Partner API=
s are used by another companies application.</li>
<li>Public APIs - Public APIs can be called by entities that may have no di=
rect or indirect relationship with the bank and expose only publicly availa=
ble information. For example ATM locations, branch locations etc.&nbsp;<str=
ong>Note that Public APIs cannot call private (Capability, Information APIs=
)</strong></li>
<li>Capability APIs - These&nbsp;APIs encapsulate business processes, busin=
ess rules etc. These APIs typically call one or more information APIs and a=
re reused across channels. This layer may contain state accessed via an API=
.&nbsp;For example, a capability API encapsulating a business process would=
 require the&nbsp;current step of the process to be stored.</li>
<li>Information APIs - The APIs perform CRUDS (create, read, update, delete=
 and search) operations on entities. For example, retrieving and updating c=
ustomer details. These&nbsp;APIs are called by partner, experience and capa=
bility APIs and are typically highly reusable.&nbsp;Access to the entity is=
 ONLY allowed via an API. Note that Information APIs&nbsp;ONLY return/accep=
t canonical values for reference data - please refer to&nbsp;<a href=3D"htt=
ps://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/mesh/Pattern+7%3A+Reference+Data=
+Cache+Pattern" rel=3D"nofollow">Pattern 7: Reference Data Cache Pattern</a=
>.=20
<ol>
<li>Information APIs are split into two physical APIs. One of the APIs does=
 read and search, the other does create, update and delete. This aligns wit=
h the&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" style=3D"text-decoration: none;" href=
=3D"https://martinfowler.com/bliki/CQRS.html" rel=3D"nofollow">CQRS Pattern=
&nbsp;</a>. The&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/displ=
ay/MESH/API+Naming+Standards" rel=3D"nofollow">naming convention&nbsp;</a>f=
or Information APIs outlines how the APIs are named and has some more infor=
mation.&nbsp;Major reasons we considered &nbsp;for this decision are ,=20
<ol>
<li><strong>Security</strong>&nbsp;=E2=80=93 &nbsp;&nbsp;Having read and wr=
ite separate APIs allows to set access permission properly . If we leave th=
e write operations in the same APIs, all the read consumers will also get a=
ccess to those.</li>
<li><strong>Scalability</strong>&nbsp;- Read APIs require more TPS , so sep=
arating them helps to scale them better</li>
<li><strong>Different Cadences for Build</strong>&nbsp;- Read APIs are reus=
ed and extended heavily. If the write operations are combined into same API=
, all those endpoints require regression testing.</li>
</ol></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/%3CDRAFT%=
3E+Information+API+Advocated+Positions" rel=3D"nofollow">Information API ad=
vocated positions</a>.</li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279292">API Ownership</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"a754afe0-7384-4b32-acf3-e4bd6c8d=
0746-1203279292">
<p>An API belongs to a Domain.&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>The Domain is aligned with Line of Business.</li>
<li>The Domain Architect is responsible for managing new components within =
their domain, and any technical debt for existing components.</li>
<li>The Domain Owner represents the people responsible for maintaining and =
providing ongoing support for the API on <span>Westpac Mesh</span>. The Dom=
ain Owner and Delegates are responsible for approving, managing support tea=
ms and development teams for their components.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Domain Owner&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>Every API within Westpac goes through a lifecycle. It is the Owners resp=
onsibility to ensure that this lifecycle is managed to ensure the impact to=
 consumers of the API is minimised.</p>
<ol>
<li>Certificate management - The Domain Owner is responsible for the orderi=
ng of the certificate for an API.</li>
<li>Capacity Management - TPS , rate limit etc . It is the owners responsib=
ility to ensure that both these TPS limits are being set appropriately.&nbs=
p;</li>
<li>If these are not provided by the owner, the platform will&nbsp;<strong>=
default to 5TPS</strong>&nbsp;for all capacity limits. That is, the API wil=
l be limited to 5TPS and each consumer will be limited to 5TPS.</li>
<li>Quality Management -&nbsp; the owner is responsible for the quality of =
the APIs being produced</li>
<li>Consumption Management</li>
<li>Support Management</li>
</ol>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Domain Architect </strong></p>
<p>Solution Architects are responsible for delivering a solution design to =
meet a business need.&nbsp;This will often take them across domains such as=
 customer, payments, group operations etc. The risk is that with their focu=
s on designing a solution, an incoherent set of APIs is delivered from an o=
rganisation perspective,. For example, APIs that duplicate functionality.</=
p>
<p>To mitigate this risk, the Domain Architect(s) work with the Solution Ar=
chitect to ensure&nbsp;a solution that aligns with&nbsp;the organisations d=
irection and meets the business need.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Domain Architect's primary roles are ,</p>
<ul>
<li>Ensures that changes to existing APIs are architecturally sound.</li>
<li>Ensures that new APIs are architecturally sound and belong to their dom=
ain.</li>
<li>Ensures that the &nbsp;API Portfolio for a domain is consistent.</li>
<li>Ensures that technical debt within the domain API portfolio is being ac=
tively managed.</li>
</ul>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279293">Your role as a Westpac Mesh Designer</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"a754afe0-7384-4b32-acf3-e4bd6c8d=
0746-1203279293">
<h2 id=3D"YourroleasaWestpacMeshDesigner-Overview"><strong>Overview</strong=
></h2>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" width=
=3D"468" src=3D"130a4b9aef9058ccf2b4023d793863b04f29c9565c2b376c77ed78971a7=
4a1db" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279293/3.png?version=3D1=
&amp;modificationDate=3D1666757984527&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment=
-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1221643264" data-linked-resource-ve=
rsion=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-d=
efault-alias=3D"3.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.=
au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-co=
ntainer-id=3D"1203279293" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"4" alt=
=3D"" height=3D"208"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"YourroleasaWestpacMeshDesigner-YourroleasaWestpacMeshDesigner"><s=
trong>Your role as a Westpac Mesh Designer</strong></h2>
<p><strong>API designers</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>are responsible for com=
pleting the details of the high level API design provided by the API archit=
ect. Architects will typically identify the broad structure of the API, whi=
ch covers the resources, the associated HTTP methods (verbs) which act on t=
he resources and the expected outcome (response) for each method. Designers=
 will work with the architects and consumers to agree on the low level deta=
ils such as the fields required for the request and response along with spe=
cific error scenarios which need to be supported.</p>
<p><strong>API designers</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>typically focus on ques=
tions like<span>&nbsp;</span><em>=E2=80=9CWhat does this service need to do=
?=E2=80=9D</em><span>&nbsp;</span>or<span>&nbsp;</span><em>=E2=80=9CWhat do=
es this service need to provide?=E2=80=9D</em>, while<span>&nbsp;</span><st=
rong>API&nbsp;Consumers</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>are focused on<span>&nbs=
p;</span><em>=E2=80=9CHow can I use this API to do what I need?=E2=80=9D</e=
m>, or more accurately,<span>&nbsp;</span><em>=E2=80=9CHow can I spend the =
bare minimum of effort to get what I need out of this API?=E2=80=9D</em>.</=
p>
<p>API designers will typically focus on the following:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Understanding the<span>&nbsp;</span></strong><strong>important =
details of the application</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>(High level Design Do=
cumentation) for which an API is to be created, so that an informed decisio=
n can be&nbsp;made as to what functionality needs to be exposed, how it nee=
ds to be exposed, and what functionality can instead be left out.</li>
<li><strong>Modelling this functionality&nbsp;</strong>in an API that addre=
sses all use cases that come up in the real world, following the RESTful pr=
inciples as closely as possible.</li>
<li><strong>Best practices and patterns&nbsp;</strong>for modern API design=
.</li>
<li><strong>Understanding the business vision</strong>, value for a well-sc=
oped business domain, and translating it to a&nbsp;great API Design.</li>
<li><strong>Improving Developer Experience (DX)<span>&nbsp;</span></strong>=
to ensure they can work quickly and more easily.</li>
</ol>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"158" src=3D"ec9e02227e93f69fc5a17ab27152dedc489df7d243b17ff4e8fdf452d4=
12e6cb" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279293/image2021-8-10_1=
4-13-57.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571073227&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279296" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-8-10_14-13-57.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279293" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"YourroleasaWestpacMeshDesigner-Deliverables"><strong>Deliverables=
</strong></h2>
<p>API Designers will deliver the following <strong>artefacts</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Swagger spec </strong>describing the API interface, according t=
o Westpac Mesh&nbsp;standards. Allows capability to generate code from Swag=
ger and is based on the<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/proj=
ects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse/examples" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"n=
ofollow"> Golden Template</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Technical documentation</strong> showing the internal design de=
tails required for the API based on Westpac Mesh&nbsp;Templates. This inclu=
des details such as: sequence diagrams, interface to provider mapping, and =
business logic.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"YourroleasaWestpacMeshDesigner-HandoverfromArchitecttoDesigner"><=
strong>Handover from Architect to Designer</strong></h2>
<p><strong><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embed=
ded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbna=
il" draggable=3D"false" height=3D"190" src=3D"ba92e814f4f002a2ed279bdfe406c=
bc2d883fed4e736bcf18fcc29f63766dd67" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachment=
s/1203279293/arch-to-designer.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D166357=
1073083&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resou=
rce-id=3D"1203279294" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resour=
ce-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"arch-to-design=
er.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked=
-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1=
203279293" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" width=3D"3=
00"></span></strong></p>
<p>A meeting should be scheduled for a formal handover to be initiated. Thi=
s meeting should provide a walk through by the architect of the high level =
use cases for the API for context what the API is intending to support and =
how it fits in the overall solution.</p>
<p>It is <strong>your responsibility</strong> to schedule a handover meetin=
g with the architect.</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">At a minimum the following pieces of =
information for the API must be provided in the meeting before a design of =
an API can begin:</span></p>
<ul>
<li>Endorsed API names</li>
<li>Endorsed Resources and operations of the API</li>
<li>Business Owner, Domain Owner and Support Team details</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"YourroleasaWestpacMeshDesigner-HandoverfromDesignertoDeveloper"><=
strong>Handover from&nbsp;</strong><strong>Designer to Developer</strong></=
h2>
<p><strong><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embed=
ded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbna=
il" draggable=3D"false" height=3D"292" src=3D"b47a09c5a656fb656a2b0dedec3c4=
4ad9efb7003dcd1a15caaf9b7b784c7147b" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachment=
s/1203279293/designer-to-dev.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571=
073157&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resour=
ce-id=3D"1203279295" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resourc=
e-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"designer-to-dev=
.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-r=
esource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"120=
3279293" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" width=3D"468=
"></span></strong></p>
<p>It is <strong>your responsibility</strong> to schedule a meeting with th=
e developer.</p>
<p>Designers to complete the following steps:</p>
<ul>
<li>Create a page for detailed design documentation under -&nbsp;<a href=3D=
"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/WDPREGO/WDP+API+Design+Regis=
ter" rel=3D"nofollow">Westpac Mesh API Design Register</a>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Get the specification reviewed by a Chapter Lead</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
</div>
